org.jrobin.core
Class FetchPoint

java.lang.Object
  org.jrobin.core.FetchPoint
Deprecated. This class is deprecated since 1.2.0 and might be removed from future releases of JRobin. You don't need this class if you fetch RRD data with the fetchData() method from the FetchRequest class

public class FetchPoint
extends java.lang.Object

Class to represent data source values for the specific timestamp. Objects of this class are created during the fetching process. See fetch() method of the FetchRequest class.
